# Command journal_viewer

## What does this command do:

TUI tool for systemd journals

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: sudo dnf install -y ncurses-devel && git clone --depth=1 https://github.com/nilseuropa/systemd_commander /tmp/sdc_build && cmake -S /tmp/sdc_build -B /tmp/sdc_build/build -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX="$HOME/.local" && cmake --build /tmp/sdc_build/build -j$(nproc) && cmake --install /tmp/sdc_build/build
For Raspberry Pi install using: sudo apt install -y libncursesw5-dev cmake g++ && git clone --depth=1 https://github.com/nilseuropa/systemd_commander /tmp/sdc_build && cmake -S /tmp/sdc_build -B /tmp/sdc_build/build -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX="$HOME/.local" && cmake --build /tmp/sdc_build/build -j$(nproc) && cmake --install /tmp/sdc_build/build

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/.local/bin/journal_viewer
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.local/bin/journal_viewer

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/nilseuropa/systemd_commander

## Command options

journal_viewer                         # launch TUI
journal_viewer --version               # show version
journal_viewer --unit ssh.service      # filter by unit
journal_viewer --namespace robot       # set journal namespace

